        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 10:52PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1052 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Gap Of The Mountain to 9 miles southwest
of Talladega National Forest to near Arcola to near Myrtlewood.
Movement was northwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Calera, Clanton, Demopolis, Montevallo, Brent, Eutaw, Centreville,
Jemison, Greensboro, Jefferson, Thorsby, Wilton, Forkland, Akron,
Boligee, Myrtlewood, Gap Of The Mountain, American Village,
Thornhill, and Brierfield Ironworks Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
central and southwestern Alabama.</instruction>
